# 1) Audit entire workspace SEO
/audit-pseo
Analyze the whole project for:
- URL structure
- PSEO readiness
- metadata quality
- structured data gaps
- internal linking opportunities
- high-paying salary consistency
Provide a prioritized list of fixes.

# 2) Improve metadata for open route
/improve-metadata
Analyze the open file. Improve metadata using rules and templates from .chatgpt-rules.
Respect high-paying positioning and user intent.

/improve-metadata-ask
Propose metadata changes but DO NOT modify the file until I confirm.

# 3) Add JSON-LD schema to job detail
/add-job-schema
Analyze job detail page. Add a safe JobPosting schema with available salary, role, and location data.

# 4) Add JSON-LD to slice/list page
/add-itemlist-schema
Generate an ItemList schema referencing job URLs or slice URLs for the open file.

# 5) Strengthen on-page SEO content
/optimize-content
Analyze on-page content for:
- user intent,
- keyword alignment,
- LSI keywords,
- structure (H1/H2),
- internal linking.
Propose improved content following .chatgpt-rules.

/rewrite-content
Rewrite content inline using SEO best practices, high-pay positioning, and LSI keywords.

# 6) Propose PSEO routes (safe mode)
/suggest-pseo
List potential new role/salary/geo/company slices that follow the rules.
DO NOT modify code until I approve.

# 7) Safe code refactor
/safe-refactor-open-file
Analyze open file. Suggest minimal, safe improvements.
Make NO changes until I confirm.

/apply-refactor
After confirmation, rewrite the file safely.

# 8) i18n planning
/plan-i18n
Propose a localization strategy based on current routes, without editing code.

# 9) Internal linking improvement
/improve-links
Analyze open page and propose internal links that strengthen PSEO without disrupting layout.

# END OF COMMANDS (v1.0)
